author: Kristi
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2019
review_content: We only had our tv and cable boxes plugged in. I heard a noise like static to find this was catching on fire! I chose 1 stars for these only because I had to. I give it a fat zero and a fire hazard.
title: Horrible. Almost fought my house on fire!

author: Amazon Customer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2019
review_content: I have about 6 of the old version of this extension cord/surge protector.The old version had several unbeatable features:--swivel head so you could have the cord angled in the right direction--flat head so you could put furniture against the outlet--long cord so you could use it behind a sofa and still have enough cord to plug things in.The new version is more than twice the width.  It's absolutely huge.  Not really flat at all.The new version has NO swivel head.  It's locked in the down position.  :(The new version is so thick at the head that's it awkward to plug in and almost impossible to plug in without touching the prongs as you push it into the socket which is incredibly dangerous.I thought perhaps I ordered the wrong brand but my old ones all have GE stamped on them, so they just made significant changes to make the product inferior.  :(
title: New version is a poor comparison to the old one

author: Emma Walsh
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2018
review_content: For the first two months, we thought this was fine; the protected light was on, everything stayed in place, life was fine. But then we had a storm and the power turned off and back on fairly quickly, but both our gaming system and sound-bar that had been plugged in are no longer functioning. So much for "protected." We wanted this to be so helpful, but it couldn't even last through one storm!
title: didn't hold up in a storm!

author: J
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 30, 2018
review_content: I recently bought a bakers rack to go right outside my tiny kitchen, and by moving my microwave and Keurig to it, I freed up some much needed counter space.  But there's no outlet on that side of the narrow wall it's against, and while I could snake the rather short microwave cord back around to the kitchen outlet, my similarly short cord on the Keurig had nowhere to go.  So I figured another power strip was in order.  I didn't much care about surge protection, but this one caught my eye because the plug is flat, meaning I could plug it in behind the nearby loveseat and not risk crushing it against the wall.  The 10 foot cord was actually a bit more than I needed, and I knew that going in, but it means I was able to place it almost completely out of sight and have some cord length to spare.  It's pretty heavy duty and seems better made than the other power strips I've been using for years in different rooms.  Exactly what I needed, and at a great price.
title: The flat plug and long cord make this a perfect solution to reaching an outlet

author: Nicole
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 25, 2018
review_content: Works as described. Only issue is that it is somewhat difficult to get the plugs to go in all the way. It's not just one, but all of the outlets are this way on both of the units I purchased. Otherwise, exactly what I needed.
title: Good product for the price.

author: Gabrielle P.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 23, 2017
review_content: I first measured out how long I needed the cord to be so that I wouldn't have extra cord laying around.  Then I use my wire-staple-gun to secure the cord to the wall neatly. And last I use double-sided-sticky-Velcro and I placed it on the back of the power adapter so that it would hold in place on the wall.Came out very clean!
title: Buy!

author: Zee Lugo
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 6, 2019
review_content: BEWARE! If you try plugging in a simple, two-pronged  plug, such as a table lamp, it won't fit. At first I thought I was doing something wrong, but half-a-dozen friends and family members tried and failed.  To clarify the issue, the power strip plugs into the wall outlet with no problem. The appliances you want to use do not fit into the strip unless they have a grounded, three-prong plug.  My Echo dots, my phone chargers, and my nightstand lamps will not plug into it. Since I bought two of these for these exact items, I wasted my money, effort, and time.
title: Can't use with Echo Dot, Phone Chargers, table lamps!

author: Chrissy
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2019
review_content: I bought these to replace units that were old. I didn't expect there to be such a huge ordeal after that. I plugged my tv into one and it immediately fried my tv. I contacted Jasco to file a claim against the warranty and it was denied. They said it worked just fine, even though it didn't work when it was in my possession...not sure what type of magic they worked there but they're just terrible terrible people. They admitted to not even testing the plugs for functionality, so how does it work when they didn't actually test it to see if it worked? Fraud. Theft. Poor Customer Service. All of the above, just a huge cluster of nonsense. I will never again buy a GE product or something related tp Jasco.
title: BUYER BEWARE - Fried My TV!

author: Roberto
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 22, 2021
review_content: We bought two of these about a month ago. One to run our 3 phone chargers and one for my son's video game counsel (PS4). Both of these cords did the exact thing. There was a smell and then we noticed the issue. If we were not home I fear the house would have burned down. Neither was being used for anything that should have caused this to happen. DO NOT BUY THIS PRODUCT.
title: DO NOT BUY THESE!!!!! YOUR HOUSE COULD BURN DOWN!!!

author: Truth Seeker
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2019
review_content: Even though I hate how this power strip was made, I gave it 3 stars as it was cheap to buy and built as durable as others in its price range. The power strip is like most power strips you pay $10 bucks for. It is a cheap plastic object. The only thing heavy duty is the cord. That is OK as I paid $10 for it. However, I can't even use the product due to the male plug being configured in such a manner that I can only plug it into the bottom of a flat outlet box. However, I have multiple outlet boxes that can't use this type of plug at all and I am limited with other outlets to only being able to use this type of plug in the bottom outlet which I don't have available for most of the outlets. So, take a  look at the plug configuration on the end of this cord. The  way the plug lays down  flat with the cord and going into the outlet at an angle rather than being parallel with the cord  and going straight into the outlet means I can't use this power strip. So, make sure you look closely at the outlet you plan to use this power strip in and be sure the plug will not cause you issues.
title: Not Happy With This Power Strip. Hate How It Is Made.

author: icelion
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 3, 2020
review_content: I bought two of these, one 10ft and one 4ft for a playroom.  I was getting feedback / static from the speakers and after a lot of research realized that if the speakers and source are not on the same power circuit you can experience static feedback.  I had this very problem ... according to the message boards installing surge protectors on either end would help.  I have an Apple TV and Nintendo Switch on one strip and the TV and speakers on another.The feedback I was getting stopped instantly upon plugging the equipment into these outlets.  I was amazed, it really worked!As great as this was, it was how they performed in a recent electrical storm that really impressed me.  Both units snapped into action when lightening hit my power lines.  Each tripped the surge and not a single issue resulted for any of my equipment.  I simply reset the strip and we were back up and running after the storm.These are very well made, wall mountable (see picture) and work great!  Highly recommend.Hope this was helpful?
title: Great Surge Protector!  Storm verified.  Eliminated audio static feedback as well.

author: SA
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2018
review_content: Been using for 2 mos without issue. A few days ago the LED flickered and then went out. I tried the switch but it would not come back on and would not output power. I checked the wall socket, which was fine, so this product simply didn't last. It's been underneath my couch and was barely touched except for when plugging in phone chargers, laptops, etc.
title: After 2 mos of use, this just broke.

author: Brian Grzymkowski
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2016
review_content: I have purchased 3 of these over the course of the last 3 months (10'). The home that we moved into did not offer much in the way of lighting. We needed a number of lamps to brighten the place up and several are linked to a specific outlet for the light switch. The longer cord was a necessity for us and got everything plugged in where it needed to be. Power strip has a small blue light near the switch to indicate it is on. We tucked it under our nightstand in the bedroom just in case to minimize any overnight glow. Outlet covers spin which can be convenient if needed. Overall I am happy with it and would not hesitate to pick up another if needed.
title: Have 3 of the 10' and have been very happy with them.

author: Amazon User
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 1, 2021
review_content: Note: this review contains reviews for both the White 10ft version and the Black 8ft version of this product.White 10ft Version:The cord width is 3/8 inch. It fits very snug in a 0.37 inch cable clip (purchased separately) as shown in the photos.When shook, the item clearly had something small inside which had broken loose. I opened it up and found that it was a small piece of solder, see photos.The case has 5 Phillips head screws and 1 triangle screw.The cord is to the side and at an angle to hug the wall and give room for another plug underneath, as shown.This item works as expected. The only drawback was the loose bit of solder. The item, mainly the cord, had small and insignificant amounts of dirtiness that easily wiped off.—-Black 8ft Version:I purchased the Black 8 foot version of this product and it leads me back to the review page for the white 10 foot version so I’m adding this revision. PLEASE BE AWARE that the keyhole slots for wall hanging on the black one are upside down. So at best it can only be mounted sideways or upside down. I did not have this issue with the white one. I would NOT have purchased the black one if I had realized that. The only photo of the keyholes on the black one are on the bottom of the page, not on the top display images.I suppose you could try to modify it by cutting out a small slot for the a nail or screw to catch, like I have, but please note the electric board is immediately above that upper keyhole so you will want to avoid that with a metal screw or nail. Maybe there are other ways to mount it, like double sided tape, but the keyholes are basically useless if you want to mount it vertically upright.The black version has the same set of screws as the white one, 5 Phillips and 1 Triangle.All in all I will likely avoid GE products in the future after this. It’s inexpensive but the usability of the products is very low due to one having upside down keyholes and one having loose solder moving around freely.I will add that they have both survived one electrical storm where power went out for a few minutes several different times.
title: Inexpensive, work as expected, but will NOT buy again

author: Chris R
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 14, 2019
review_content: Okay, my bad for not looking more closely before buying, but while overall this is a fine power strip and I like the 10' cord option, the sockets all point toward the bottom of the strip vs. out to the side.The issue is if you have a large transformer, like with an apple product, or a flat plug, like with most monitors, it seems the cord for each will cover the socket next to the one you are using, whereas if the sockets were turned to point sideways you could use all six outlets. As a result, this 6-outlet power strip can turn quickly into a three outlet strip, or four if you are lucky (see picture).
title: Socket positioning doesn't allow for full use of the power strip

author: Kindle Customer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 30, 2018
review_content: My tv has issues turning on (clicks over and over for up to 5 minutes before turning on) when connected to this surge protector.  It works fine when plugging it into the wall or any other surge protector.
title: GE - Gory Electronics

author: EliteReviewsUSA
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2020
review_content: This is useful for someone who needs to plug a power cord into something but needs extra reach. My computer is placed far from the power outlet so this comes in handy. I also like having extra spare slots for the power outlets because walls usually only have 1-2 at max. These extenders help a lot. The material isn't a hard plastic but nothing heavy and tough should be hitting it hard enough to damage it because these are usually placed out of sight.I am surprised that it only costs about $12 for the longest one they have because usually when it comes to electronics and cords the larger they are the more expensive they become, usually making the price unreasonable just because you want a lengthier cord. I am glad the product isn't a rip-off that demands four times the price compared to the original/default length.
title: Extra Long Without Costing A Lot

author: E. Brizzolara
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2019
review_content: This power strip is as bad as it can be while still being functional enough to not be worth replacing. The problem is this: it will not keep plugs in. Any slight pull on a cord will disengage the plug from the strip, often only enough to keep the power from working. The number of times I've woken up to an uncharged phone because the plug has come slightly out is too many.Power runs to it. I assume it works to protect against surges (But have not experienced any). But gosh darn is this thing frustrating. Do not buy.
title: Will not keep plugs in.

author: Shay Tressa DeSimone
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 31, 2021
review_content: I purchased this GE Surge Protector with 10-Foot Extension Cord to use with an immersion water heater we ordered to warm up cold bathwater after our water heater died during the big Texas freeze of 2021. (We went a month without hot water since water heaters were on back order everywhere.) The immersion heater draws a lot of electricity (1500W) and the nearest outlet was far from our bathtub, on the far wall past the sink; so we needed a reliable extension outlet...and this GE Surge Protector proved to be the perfect solution. (It's approved to handle up to 1800W and 120V.)I particularly appreciated the on/off switch on the surge protector, which made it easy to turn off power to the immersion heater when the water was warm enough, so I didn't have to worry about unplugging the device with wet hands. I also liked the surge protector's flat plug head and angled cord, which helped the cord easily clear the sink counter above which it was plugged.When using a surge protector/extension cord with a device that draws as much power as an immersion heater, it's important to make sure you only have one device plugged into the power strip and that the power strip is the only item plugged into that particular wall outlet. We only used one of the surge protector's outlets, and kept the other 5 outlet covers rotated to keep dust and water out of the sockets. As such, we never had a problem with the circuit being overloaded.Overall, I couldn't be happier with the performance of this GE Surge Protector/Extension Cord. It reliably handled several weeks of daily immersion heater use, with the immersion heater running for 1.5 to 2 hours for each bath, once or twice per day. Now that our water heater is repaired, I moved this surge protector to my office, where I have every confidence it will do an equally good job of protecting my computer and other electronic devices. And given the price, I think it's a great value! Highly recommended.
title: High-Quality, Heavy-Duty Surge Protector/Extension Cord

author: PharmaGuy
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2020
review_content: This GE extension cord and 6 plug surge protector arrived as described. The cord length is indeed 15' and the item included 6 individual 3-prong outlets. Each outlet has a twist-lock design that keeps the outlets closed when not in use. I suppose this is a safety feature to keep young children from inserting objects into the unused outlets. Either way, they work as intended. Please note that the outlets are not designed to swivel themselves...they only rotate to allow opening/closing. You cannot adjust the prong direction to account for oddly shaped plugs. There is a blue light that indicates whether the surge protector is on/off. It is bright but not too intense that it becomes obnoxious or annoying.
title: Well-made extension cord and surge protector from GE

author: 3timesoccermom
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 27, 2021
review_content: I don't get why, but the cords I plug into this extension cord are constantly slipping out.  The cord is also very stiff and refuses to straighten - it wants to stay in a coiled position.  The socket holes are also very close together - which the photos do seem to show - but I didn't think the plugs would be so close together until I actually had it here to see and try.I like the long length but those inconveniences are too many for me.  I wish I'd bought something else.
title: Cords won't stay plugged in

author: Carol Gibbs
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 20, 2021
review_content: This is a great product and I'm very satisfied with it. This is my second purchase of this item.! The cord length is great, and the performance is as well. I would like to share what happened a week and a half or so ago with my original one. I had, among other things, a heating pad plugged into the surge strip. Later in the evening, I plugged in a steam roller device that heats water to seam your curlers. The two were too much and the steam roller device "blew!" I had always been warned about using too many items that pull alot of heat or electricity at the same time, but thought nothing of it at the moment.  The bottom line is that none of my fuses were thrown which I believe was because the surge strip did it's job and did it well!The surge strip didn't survive but nothing on it was burned, darkened or blackened, and it didn't show signs of any melting or other damage, however it didn't work again, which is a small price to pay for avoiding blown fuses or fire. This is why I replaced the first with a second just like it - same brand, same features. I am very happy with this product and would recommend it highly.
title: Perfect and performs as it should!

author: Floyd
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 20, 2020
review_content: I hate GE products. I try never to buy GE products because EVERY TIME I DO, THEY FAIL! I chumped off and bought this because I really needed a short multiplug surge protector, I didn't want to break quarantine,  and there just wasn't a lot of choice on Amazon. I plugged my microwave into this piece of &$#@!. It then proceeded to emit a loud buzzing noise from the microwave itself every time we used it.  I thought that it was the microwave and that it was about to blow up.  Then my son accidentally moved the surge protector and the buzzing went away. Yeah, it was the GE surge protector. Never again.
title: Typical GE product

author: Laura Pacetti
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 15, 2018
review_content: Piece of crap.  Plugs have to be wiggled into place.  Last one dies after 4 months.  We don't make anything anymore.  I guess I should try to find an extension cord at n antique store or make one myself.
title: Don't buy it!

author: Victoria E
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2020
review_content: I like it. The plug itself is slightly thick and due to the shape of the plug and cord, you can only plug in thinner plugs below it, but thicker cords can go above it. This matters, though!I have a lightswitch that turns on and off the bottom outlets and I couldn't use my preferred lamp because of the cord shape. And I have no ceiling light, so the bottom outlet needed to be connected to a lamp so I could see when I walked in my room at night.  Fortunately, I have two lamps.For the surge protector, I need this to be easily accessible and not able to be turned off because I turned off the lightswitch, so it has to be on top. It has the power for my TV and PS4, so I cannot improperly turn those off when using the TV as a second monitor or when playing games. Fortunately, most 2-prong outlets should fit just fine below it. And if you don't have my problem, you're probably fine and can fit everything on this outlet.It works great and I love that I can turn the outlets not in use so no one tries to electrocute themselves with their claws. I also tape ones not in use with painter's tape, though. Overall, great product and I'm glad I bought it. Had it about 2 months already and all of it works fine.
title: Great

author: Brian Hoskins
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 17, 2021
review_content: So this is just a power strip with surge protector.  There's not much to review here...overall, it works fine.  The cord is quality, the plugs don't feel like they'll fall apart, etc.  But we bought this to use with my son's computer, and in doing so we found a weird issue:  With this power cord in use, my son's desktop computer would just randomly lose all power and turn off.  Not a controlled shut down, but just instantly off.  It was really bizarre, and for a couple of days it didn't occur to me that it could be this power strip.  But it didn't do this before we started using this power strip, and so I thought to test that theory.  Sure enough, putting a different power strip in place resolved the issue - no more sudden power loss.  So I'm not sure what the deal is with this one, but it didn't like that setup.  I've used it elsewhere (with non-computer devices) and it's been fine.
title: Probably OK, but one weird issue...

author: Zachary Anderson
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 8, 2021
review_content: Useful power strip. Like any, be aware of the maximum current allowed and do not overload. I bought for the 10 foot cord length, and while I did not actually measure the cord length, 10 feet seems like a really reasonable representation of the actual length. Quite pleased by this measure.The only thing I dislike are the 1/8-turn shutters on each outlet: they are not useful or user-friendly. Instead, they provide a false sense of security without actually being tamper-resistant. A waste of plastic in my mind.Another reviewer mentioned it was great for traveling. I have never traveled with a power strip, nor do I intend to start doing so. But this power strip does offer North American universality, so theoretically it would work in multiple locations if one felt inclined to travel with their power strip(s).
title: Useful device for have for plug-in convenience

author: Mighty Mouse
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 7, 2019
review_content: I like the cord length, on/off switch and protection indicator light, all of which make this a good choice for equipment you don't want to have to replace in the event of a damaging power surge.  I DON'T like the direction of the plugs and how closely they are placed, because they won't permit fat plugs like rechargers (phone, tablet, etc.) to be placed next to each other.  Those require you to give up the use of one or more of the nearest plugs.  When you have several things to plug in to the same energy source, but that wouldn't be in use at the same time, (so you would never be overloading the power strip) this is not the best outlet strip for you.  More spacing between plugs and rotating plug-in direction 90 degrees would be better.
title: Basic Surge Protector if You Only Need to Plug in 3-4 Cords

author: Stephen M.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2021
review_content: This was one of the cheaper surge protectors on Amazon when I purchased it. I did not need anything fancy, just something that would do the job. That said, it does not appear to be very well made, despite that it is from General Electric.I do like how the plugs have a swivel feature that you can use to close them off from anything getting into the slots. But I do not like that there is no indicator light that the surge protector is on and that the things I have plugged in are grounded.Ultimately, this is a decent product but you get what you pay for. An extra $3-$5 might go a long way in better securing, or at least indicating security, for the appliances you plug into it. But if you need something that does the job and want to spend very little money, this will do the job.
title: Does the job

author: JAQ3
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 20, 2021
review_content: Great power outlet with 10 foot extension cord that is thick and won’t breakdown in you. Cord can be easily folded and wrapped if full extension is not being used. This power strip is very Versatile, and have used in multiple rooms. Has 6 outlets for 2 or 3 prong plugs, Power on/off switch, and plug covers that swivel to close the plug ports that are not in use.no USB ports. I use this cord for my tv, fan, and phone charger. The blue light indicator is bright for me at night, but it is not bothersome for everyone I show it to. I like to sleep in total darkness, so I put a few pieces on duct tape over the light indicator. Perfect for me now. Excellent product! Great Quality and Worth the money! Great Value! I bought two of these! One I use strictly for a treadmill in the living room. Buy it, it’s worth it!
title: Awesome power strip! Super long cord, flat wall plug, 6 Outlets.

author: Emma Flener
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 2, 2019
review_content: Whoever packed this, crammed it into the box. Thats probably the reason it doesnt work. Tried different outlets and everything. No luck.
title: Arrived damaged.

author: MOO MOO
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2021
review_content: Maybe Our wall sockets are old.  And make unplugging Any appliance difficult.  Plus almost any appliance with trip the circuit breakers.  BLACKOUT!  NO ELECTRICITY!So, We ordered a surge protector, one for every room we need to plug in an appliance - blow dryer, blender, microwave, etc.I almost got electrocuted trying to unplug an appliance from our wall socket.  How?  Why?  What happened!!!My mini fan, It wouldn't unplug, and I grabbed the nearest thing, a pair of metal scissors to pry the plug out of the wall electric socket.  The minute the blades contacted the plug.  BOOM!Next thing you know, The scissors flew across the room.  When I picked it up, it had burnt marks and dents.  Yikes!  I almost got electrocuted.Thank God the scissor had plastic handles.  So, now you know why I use a surge protector in every outlet.  And it stays plugged in.
title: Prevents accidents.  Very good if you have kids

author: Sumit
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2021
review_content: The six slots are basically useless if you connect two large adapters. Large adapters take up at least three sockets. Seems like there was no thought put into the design. How hard can it be to align the sockets correctly!!! Can’t even return it!!!
title: DO NOT BUY

author: Brian S.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2020
review_content: I wanted several switched power outlets a fairly long ways from the nearest power outlet. This does that job nicely. I sometimes plug things in which I want a quick+nearby way to turn off if they start misbehaving, which this is helpful for.The outlet covers are one of the less annoying styles I've encountered, if you're plugging things in when you can see+access the power strip. That works for my use case, but if you're going to be plugging things in without very good access they will be pretty annoying. They turn freely between the "open" and "closed" positions. That means you can leave them "open" just fine, but if you bump them while plugging something in they tend to move around so then you can't plug it in at all. I also question how effective this will be at stopping kids from sticking things in the outlets, because it's basically 50/50 whether random poking leaves it "open" or "closed".I don't care at all about the surge protection abilities (or lack thereof).
title: Nice power strip with a long cord

author: Vality
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 15, 2021
review_content: I'm using this surge protector in a bedroom, so this may effect use case. Overall the design is nice, physically lightweight and holds plugs securely but without excessive insertion force. For the price it's a very decent device.I only have 3 small qualms stopping me from giving it a 5. Specifically, the LED light on the protector is excessively bright, to the point it is hard to sleep with one in the room. Secondly the off switch (which turns off power to all ports) has an extremely low actuation force and I often had it trigger accidentally while plugging something in. Finally the cords I got made a plastic rattling when gently shaken, so I suspect there might be a slight quality control issue.
title: Effective good value surge protector with slight flaws

author: Mike
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2018
review_content: Works well. Only complaint when you plug something in it will not always go in all the way and requires extra force to get the plug all the way in. Great for open areas, but hard to use if tucked away under desk.
title: Great for open areas

author: Eduardo H
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 18, 2019
review_content: I like the extension chord as it mainly meets my needs. As described, it's 6 feet long, it has the locking outlets, and it is flat. The one thing the ad doesn't mention is that although the chord is flat, the chord angles to the right, which may be issue depending on your application. In my case I needed the chord to angle left, (or down) so that I could have a cleaner look. Not a major issue in the greater scheme of things, but it would have been nice to have the information, and/or to have the option to select the return angel.
title: Return Right, is that what you need?

author: R. Roberts
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2018
review_content: Initial impressions -PROS:  Seems well made.  Heavy duty cord, although rather stiff.  Wings around switch reduce risk of accidental shut off.CONS: Blue light is big and bright - annoying in a bedroom.  The "Limited Lifetime Warranty" is a joke.  It basically says - all surge protectors wear out ... "In this event, the Limited-Lifetime Warranty is no longer valid and the surge protector should be replaced."
title: Limited Lifetime Warranty is a joke

author: Rachel
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2021
review_content: I purchased the power strip on Feb 14, 2020. At first, it tripped a few times, and I thought it was protecting me from power surges, but then it started to trip every few weeks and I couldn't run more than 3 devices on the power strip. Then it started to trip every day until I couldn't get it to stay on. I had to replace it.It was finally no longer operational around December 20, 2020. I opted to replace it, and wrote the review later because I finally was able to replace it with another different brand. It was a waste of money. I guess this power strip is a reflection of 2020. Doesn't distribute power evenly and eventually breaks.
title: Broke in less than a year

author: Amy
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2018
review_content: I purchased this item because it has long cord. I like it overall but the small bright blue light above switch really bothers me in the dark! I had to put dark tape over it.
title: Super bright blue switch light!!!

author: nick
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 22, 2020
review_content: I bought these because of the cord length. I’m using them mainly for my tv/media setups. I was surprised to see when they arrived that the power plug has a slim design that sits pretty close to the wall. That’s great but the weird thing is that they are permanently angled to the right rather than straight down or being able to rotate like others I have seen. This has made the cord a little awkward to work with and actually takes away some of the length.
title: Weird cord configuration

author: jules
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2018
review_content: Quality item!! Very nice thick sturdy cord, rotating outlets to keep out dust & debris. We ran this behind our sofa over to the wall plug and slid it up under the edge. We needed the length, but not quite as many outlets. We can pull it out and turn on when needed. Switch lights up when on and is off when power is off. Definitely a must have item with a couple of teens around and they always need a charger!! One glance is all you need to be sure it is off and not using electricity.
title: Quality item, and well made!

author: Victoria
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2021
review_content: Cord length was great for my work setup. Everything was fine until I plugged in a new lamp. Two sleeping laptops, a not-in-use phone charger, and a salt lamp was apparently too much for this power strip. Fortunately all my devices are fine. Rated at 15amps, should have only had around 2 amps running through it when it blew. However, if there was a feedback, it did exactly what it was supposed to do, in a sense, and sacrificed itself to save my stuff.
title: Worked, but maybe not as intended... Need a new one already and my room smells funny now.

author: Spender of Money
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2020
review_content: Was looking for surge protectors with a long chord.My daughter moved into a super cute apartment, but it had little to no outlets, and no outlets in her room. I got these for her as a sort of housewarming gift. Now she can charge her phone at night, within reach.
title: Bought for the chord length

author: Amazon Customer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2019
review_content: Having a surge protector with a 10-foot cord may not seem like a big deal, but it is.  I'd never been able to find one with a cord longer than 3 feet!  I live in an old house that doesn't have a lot of outlets; the "box" has been updated so the house can handle the demand on the electricity, but that didn't give me more outlets.  This allows me to plug in as many lights, and devices that I need without having to arrange my furniture so that everything is close to an outlet.  Never seen one before - until I looked on Amazon!
title: Finally!

author: SAVVY  SHOPPER
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 5, 2021
review_content: I saw quite a bit of negative reviews for this product. Well, I decided to buy it anyway. I have not had any problems with the surge protector. I’ve been using it for 8 months. However, I use it responsibly. I make sure to align the covers to the holes for the outlet. So I don’t have to force my plug into the outlet portion. I also close the covers after usage. I do not overload the surge protector with multiple plugs. When I am done using the surge protector I simply turn off the power to it. However I do leave it plugged into the wall but the power is off again. Therefore, I haven’t had any electrical fires. Or damage to any of my appliances. So I can honestly say that I am quite happy with my purchase.
title: Treat with Care and it will worked for you.

author: Brian Quinlan
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 7, 2021
review_content: I read reviews stating plugs slip out, but bought the power strip anyways. I found that it holds plug tight. General Electric should be able to manufacture a power strip, and they can! The child-proof covers are not an annoyance. They turn easily. I didn't need them, but they haven't been any problem. Can children and pets get shocked? I guess it happens.
title: Buy It - Holds Plugs Tight

author: Sunny
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2019
review_content: This is a great power outlet strip. I love the flat plug design. I have the flat plug plugged in behind some furniture which normally wouldn't accommodate a regular plug. That is definitely a handy feature. I only just started using this so I can't comment about the surge protection feature, plus where I live, I've never had a surge protector fry on me, so I doubt our electrical connection here is that unstable. My only complaint is that the power LED is way too bright. I have a neurological condition that takes away some light perception in my eyes so it always looks like I have sunglasses on. I can see the power LED on this thing at night on my ceiling (when I barely have much usable night vision left), so this is really saying something. Yes, the LED is annoying especially when you are trying to sleep. You can tape over it, but I wish GE's design team thought about it before putting in such a bright LED as a power indicator.
title: Great outlet strip, but the power light is super bright.

author: J. Adams
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 31, 2019
review_content: Just like the reviewer from a few months ago, this almost started a house fire. I plugged it into the wall, plugged in my laptop and a computer speaker system, and immediately started hearing a weird static-like noise. Within a minute, white smoke started pouring from my subwoofer and I smelled burning plastic. I unplugged everything, but had to air my house out for the whole day, and my sound system is fried. The sound system that lasted me 8 years with absolutely no issues, plugged into an older, shorter power strip.Absolutely horrible, dangerous product. It cost me $45 for new computer speakers, and ruined my day.
title: Fried my sound system and almost started a house fire

author: Charlotte
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 25, 2020
review_content: I really like this surge protector. I bought it because of the flat plug. The one I had a work stuck straight out and my rolling files kept getting caught on it, so this one is a great improvement. The only reason I’m giving it 4 stars instead of 5 is because it is hard to push the plugs all the way into the surge protector strip. Fortunately, I won’t be needing to do a lot of plugging and unplugging, but if I did, that would be a big drawback. You never want to feel like you’re forcing a plug into the receptacle.
title: Flat plug is great

author: Joe Chasko
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2021
review_content: Although it cleans the wall mountable, the holes on the back will take only Bert small screws (not included). I had to grind down number eights to get them to fit but the real flaw is that it’s made backwards. If mounted vertically, the cord comes out of the top! Under what possible installation will the cord be coming down to the mounted strip? Brain dead engineering.  On the plus side it has a nice heavy cord that has these annoying rotating safety covers. Sheesh. I also found that the distance between the screws must be 7 3/4 less a 16th. What the hell.
title: Not very “wall mountable“

author: Katheryn c
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 20, 2019
review_content: I like the fact that the plugs rotate but the wall plug is a bit hard to navigate if you aren't looking directly at it so trying to plug it in behind say a shelf is tough. It seems to work well and everything I've plugged in seems to get plenty of power. The socket is secure enough to where a little tug on your phone charger wont unplug it. My main issue and reason for minus one star is the fact that the power switch lights up very bright to the point where it illuminates the whole room in the dark
title: Powers up well

author: Rangermenace
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 27, 2021
review_content: Its a power strip, flat power plug which is always welcome all should have this, twist cover closer for unused outlets another good addition to keep dust, help against liquid spills or anything else from electricity, 800 joules Surge protection for your electronics with integrated circuit breaker shut off against overloads and one button to turn off power for all plugs. Everything you buy a power strip for with some extras not always found Perfect for when simply more outlets are required for low draw devices.
title: GE 6-Outlet Surge Protector, 4 Ft Extension Cord, Power Strip, 800 Joules, Flat Plug

author: DMagee
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 9, 2021
review_content: It’s been 8 months since I purchased and one of the outlets are not working. I don’t  know if it ever worked because I didn’t check... I don’t need all of the outlets, I primarily use only two randomly, however, when my phone didn’t charge I was at a loss then I discovered it was the outlet. IDK if that is common but my job uses them (IDK the Mfr) but that’s why I purchased once I began to work at home. I like the switch to turn off to reserve electricity, I’m unhappy about the loss of an outlet, Otherwise I am satisfied.
title: Losing Options after 8 Months

author: Belle
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2020
review_content: Received a generic surge protector that looked dirty and looked used. I didn't even attempt to use it because it just looked very poorly made and cheap. I wasn't going to risk ruining my electronics with this garbage.The seller should be ashamed of themselves selling fire hazards to people. Don't buy this, just go to Home Depot or something and get a legit GE product.
title: FAKE- fire hazard

author: Bruce Grembowski
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2019
review_content: While I had to give this 5 stars for its 10' cord length,  it gets only two stars overall. After just over a year of use, one of the sockets failed when I inserted a plug slightly crooked.This is just a symptom of its overall inexpensive design. The supposed safety caps that twist to cover the outlets don't lock into place, as noted by another reviewer.The cord is a relatively stiff PVC, but is functional enough.The blue light when it has power is annoying, as noted by a different reviewer, but not intolerably so in the day.Overall, if you need an inexpensive, probably not very good at surge protection, power strip, then this is for you!
title: You Get What You Pay For

author: Primer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 20, 2019
review_content: This power strip is great, worked perfectly until my bird chewed the plastic off part of the cord, making it unsafe to use (and thankfully she didn’t hurt herself).  So I’m on my second power strip of the same type and will keep a much closer eye on her when she’s hanging out by the cord!  I love how the outlet covers rotate so nothing can get inside them (ideal in my bird room to keep out feather dust or food debris).  The blue light is also handy as a night light so the birds don’t freak out as easily if they’re startled in the dark.  Overall great power strip, hope this one lasts longer than the first!
title: Had to buy another after my bird chewed the cord

author: HonestReviews
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 19, 2021
review_content: If you're looking for a simple power strip, you won't find much to complain about with this one. It was longer than I needed, which I was fine with. It doesn't have any fancy features to mess with. Overall, it's pretty basic, which is reflected in the price, and it does what it's supposed to do. No complaints here.
title: Nothing to complain about

author: Cyn Johnson
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 13, 2018
review_content: The cable length is great, and the quality is good. However, the sockets are so close together that only very narrow plugs will fit next to each other. Adaptors will cover 2-3 sockets each.
title: Crowded sockets are a problem

author: Danielle M
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2020
review_content: Got this to mount on the side of a giant built-in bed where the outlet was centered behind the bed. (We just moved into this house). I mounted it with two velcro squares on the side of the bed post near my night stand, and it has worked wonderfully ever since. The bar has two mounting holes for this purpose, but I didn't want to put holes in the bed frame.The outlets turn to lock closed, which can be a good safety feature for children.Overall, I'm very satisfied with these power strips.
title: Excellent & useful

author: Kellie S
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 23, 2019
review_content: The power strip itself works fine. The reason for the 3 stars is that I was looking for an extension cord with a flat plug. The 8 ft option came up in my search for “3 foot power strip flat plug”, but I wanted a 3 foot cord, so I just used the drop down menu and selected the 3 foot option. I did not realize that the 3 foot option did not have a flat plug until I received it. I went back and looked at the picture and, sure enough, the 3 foot option had a normal plug (but other lengths had the flat plug).  So, while this was technically my fault because I should have checked, I feel like it was a little bait and switch and this the 3 stars.
title: Make sure to check the plug style before buying

author: PD
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2020
review_content: Bought one of these surge protectors approx a year ago.  Worked(s) great.  Needed another one for another room and noticed that I could could get a two-pack for a good price.  So I did.  Then sure enough, shortly after, I needed the extra one.  These also come in different cord lengths so you can choose which is best for you. Three times a winner in my book.
title: Three times a winner

author: 0re0
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2020
review_content: My home is in Canada and I ordered the item in Hong Kong (work based). It is a lapse on my part not to check the voltage rating thinking most of these items are on auto voltage rating (110V~240V / 50~60Hz).Upon plugging mine "boom"! Gone not even in 60 seconds. I can still probably use it replacing the the fuse inside but would not bother considering the purchase price.Product description / specification should at least mention the power specs.Probably a good product but future buyers please take note before clicking "Order".
title: Product voltage rating

author: isaac
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 22, 2021
review_content: I was very unimpressed with the last two GE power strips I bought, so much so that I returned them and called customer service to offer feedback on the design. I was afraid this would perhaps be the case again, but upon unpacking the extremely plain box, I deemed this strip acceptable, and has been working fine for a few weeks now. The one criticism I do have is that the plastic feels a bit flimsy, and the high gloss finish is often a hallmark of that property.
title: Moves power 20 feet, safely.

author: E. N. M.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 22, 2020
review_content: I needed a surge protector with a longer cord and wanted one that plugs in flush to the wall. This fit the bill and was relatively easy to mount. I would have liked it more if it came with a drilling template but w/e.ConsNo USB ports which I overlooked when buying.  Not a huge deal.Doesn’t have a spaced out port for bigger power bricks.All plugs are in a line vs perpendicular to each other. Power bricks will take up multiple plugsAll in all, this fit the bill for the price I wanted to pay.  No complaints.
title: Great product

author: Phillip A. Lamb
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 6, 2020
review_content: These were purchased for stage power because of the length of the cord and the name of the manufacturer which used to mean quality.  I purchased two of them.  One works decent, but has one of the outlets that does not work with any 2 or 3 prong cable plugged in.  The other one has 3 that do not work with any cable.  I would of returned them but it was past that point with Amazon.  DO NOT PURCHASE!!!  These are NOT a quality product.  These should not be for sale.  Pretty sure they are not a safe product.
title: Not a quality product

author: Jerry L
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2020
review_content: I needed an extension cord and power strip/surge protector. I wanted a strong, tough cord with 12ga. wires that would stand up to a high power load if needed. This seems to be just what I was looking for. The 10' cord is big and tough, the strip isn't too big and has the covers to close off individual power receptacles to keep trash out. A good product worth the money. I regret that I didn't get a black one though. So far no problems at all. Don't expect any because of the way this product is made. Worth the price and the shipping time is very good.
title: Good bargin.

author: Jenny K.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 25, 2020
review_content: Some reviewers said that the plug they received is not the flat one as described/pictured on the product page so I was hesitant when ordering.  Thankfully, the one I received is exactly as pictured, with a square flat plug.  The cord itself is a bit thicker than I thought, but that is not an issue for me.
title: Plug came exactly as pictured

author: Bacon SF
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 27, 2021
review_content: I overloaded the circuit and this saved my electronics, but broke immediately.My other surge protectors would just shut off and I can manually turn it back on.I gave it two stars as it protected my electronics from getting fried
title: Broke after one surge!

author: Bethany Moore
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2020
review_content: This is the 3rd surge protector of this specific brand that I have purchased, and it's because they are so perfect for what I need. I live in a place that often has power outages and have actually had a few electronics fried because of not being plugged into a surge protector. Since using these, I haven't had one single issue. They're always the length advertised and they always seem to do what they advertise as well.
title: As advertised

author: Shelby
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2021
review_content: Works like it should, the length of the cord was perfect.  My significant other wanted a TV in a room with windows or closet on every wall soooo I installed a motorized, drop down ceiling mount to put one on.  I had attic access with a receptacle approximately 15' away, this was perfect.  Made for an easy install and helped me maintian moderate hero status in my household, not an easy position to maintain.
title: No frills, works great!  Perfect for my ceiling mounted TV with motorized bracket!

author: Dragonfly
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 16, 2019
review_content: I don't love this power strip because 1) the cord is so ridiculously stiff I can't get it to open up or lay flat, 2) the 3 prong plug areas are pointing in a direction that is opposite what my larger plug items need, causing me to have to cover up 3 outlets with just 1 item, and 3) the super bright blue light that beams out and disturbs my sleep (I had to figure out a way to cover it up).
title: I don't love this power strip.

author: Andrew
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 20, 2021
review_content: I ordered this after searching local retail stores without success. At the time we needed something that had a longer cord due to the limited access to the wall outlets in our old apartment. Overall this worked great and I’m sure we’ll find uses for it at our new place too! If you need a surge protector with a bit of a longer cord I highly recommend this.
title: Great product!

author: sheelah1
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 9, 2021
review_content: I use my cord as an on and off button for my iron. My iron stays plugged in and I use it for my quilting. I brought the cord up and attached it to my small ironing area and I don't have to worry about forgetting to turn the iron on or off It's right there where I can see it and this is a perfect item for multiple electric appliances to turn off at once.
title: Turn items on and off at cord.

author: Renee
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2021
review_content: Love the extra long cord. The only downside is that the plug that goes into the wall doesn’t rotate so the cord (for my setup where I’m using it and the socket is sideways) doesn’t run smoothly against the wall. It has to circle around the plug in the socket. I wish they would have gone one step further for the perfect product. (And I wish I had thought to look for one that rotated).
title: Good product for verticals sockets

author: Stephen
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 16, 2020
review_content: Nice heavy duty multiple outlet extension cord.  The flat plug is great to have as well as the surge protection.  the only downside I have with it is that the cord is very large and thick.  Which is a good thing if you're having a lot of power going through the wires.  Just not very flexible
title: Like the flat plug and surge protection.  Cord is really heavy

author: Carla
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 8, 2019
review_content: At the first storm, it "protected" so well that my computer's power switch fried. Cost me $250 for repair.
title: No protection whatsoever

author: :P
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2020
review_content: Bought the 20ft cable because as you may expeft the outlet is far from where I sit.Time to throw some salt:1- The twist feature on this power strip is not completly useless as I mainly use it to twist the outlets that I will never have access to because the most you can fit on this powerstrip is three connection [ Three medium sized phone chargers ].2- The blue light indicator for protection isen't a bad feature, it's about the same brightness of a dim PS4 controller. Alhough wish it was dimmer.3-The cable feels soft and I have it going around some sharp angles. So just for an extra layer of protection I wrapped it with electrical tape4- It's long, it's decent, it gets the job done
title: Long, but not the toughest

author: Laci
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 1, 2020
review_content: This product is a lifesaver. I have three in my apartment and it has made my life so easy. If I am going out of town for a week and want to reduce my electric bill I just flip the switch to turn off all of the devices plugged in. It is so nice having an extension with this many plug ins.
title: Life saver! I own 3.

author: NATALY FERNANDEZ
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2020
review_content: I’m a mobile hairdresser and needed something that would be safe to use with my blow dryer and also long enough to reach any outlets if I’m not set up close to one. This works great. I’m able to use my dryer just fine, and if it overloads the fuse, then the power chord just shuts off no harm done! There is one outlet that doesn’t work but the rest do so I just don’t plug anything in that one.
title: Works with a hair dryer

author: IIBuc_NastyII
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 24, 2019
review_content: Seems like very high quality and good value for price. Its FAR nicer and better than other cords, non surge strips, and surge strips I have that were anywhere from a few dollars cheaper to many dollars more expensive. This was definitely the best purchase.I like the little doors that swivel to cover unused sockets.Be aware it is designed to plug into a wall. The plug is well designed for that - it is low profile. However if you're plugging this in to another strip of some sort or need it adjacent to other plugs it might not fit well.
title: Real Solid

author: Amazon Customer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2021
review_content: This outlet surge protector has really helped me organize my work desk. After I started working from home, I had a lot of issues trying to have the same computer setup that I was used to back at my office. This product was able to help me connect as much as necessary so I could keep my desk's regular items without compromising the setup of my work area. The flat plug makes it easy to put it near my desk. The twist-to-close safety covers are also very neat. Lastly, the long cord was extremely helpful to place this down near my desk. I highly recommend this!
title: Great Product!

author: Brooks
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 16, 2019
review_content: Pay attention when picking the cord length, not all size come with a flat plug.The initial description said “flat plug”, I chose the length I needed, but it turned out that the 2ft. and 3ft. strips come with not flat plug (it sticks out almost 5”).I was ordering from my phone and didn’t notice in the picture that the 2 ft. strip was shown with a not flat plug.Normally I would expect the strip to have a different design just because the it’s a ft. shorter.It’s a bit annoying to deal with the exchange, otherwise it’s good.
title: Not a flat plug

author: Stephen Danner
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2020
review_content: Product works fine but the plug is not as shown in the product photos.  It is an offset plug which can only be used in one of the two outlets without blocking the adjacent outlet.  My other electronic device can also only be used in the same outlet.  Sell what you advertise!!!  I previously purchased the black version of this same product and it has the plug that plugs straight in and only ties up one outlet as advertised.  Bummer for the white product.  Another Made in China product with a GE label slapped on it.
title: Plug is not as advertised

author: Brandon W
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 10, 2019
review_content: I bought this for the cord length since the only outlet on the wall was behind a dresser. It serves its purpose. The only issue is that since it is in our bedroom next to my wife's side of the bed, she has complained that the blue power light makes it hard to sleep. The spinning child locks also feel a bit cheap, but we don't use them since we don't have children. Overall it's okay if you are on a budget and need the longer cord.
title: Great cord length, annoying light

author: artistic_baller
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 11, 2020
review_content: I already posted a review indicating that the item I received was NOT what is described/sold. I ordered a new GE surge protector extension cord. What I received was not GE or new. It was a rip off cheaply made item. I don’t understand why my first review was taken down?
title: Fake used product.

author: D Patel
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 23, 2021
review_content: Just a regular outlet strip that works. The main reason I wanted to buy this was for my sensitive and expensive electronics. The rotating outlet covers is a nice feature to keep it safe from kids. Also, the plus has is angled to the right so it would be perfect for places where you have your plug on the left and your electronics on the right. I gave this a 4 star because it looked like it was used before so it wasn't in the cleanest shape which is pretty prominent when you have a white cord.
title: Works as described but looks refurbished?

author: DDR
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 14, 2020
review_content: This surge protector was an easy sell for me based upon the cord length. It's so hard to find these with cords longer than 3-6 feet! In some cases that's long enough, but to have those few extra feet can make all the difference in a room with fewer plugs! It works really well and I've yet to run into any functionality issues with either of the units I purchased. I could easily recommend these to other buyers in the market for an item like this.
title: Looks and Feels High-End

author: Mark R.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2020
review_content: We bought this primarily for the cord length. It fit our needs perfectly, connecting the closest wall outlet to an electric kettle, microwave, and coffee grinder on a table 10ft away.It has worked so well for the past year that we’ve pretty much forgotten it’s there; everything is just functional without having to worry about how far away the outlet is.This morning (One year, exactly, to the day since we purchased it, ironically) the electric kettle would not heat water and the microwave would shut off after only a few seconds. The power strip is tripping these off, which it never has before.Seems that a year of regular use is about all this thing can handle; now time to find a new 10’ power strip. Would be nice not to have to replace it every year, but I guess for the relatively cheap price I can’t complain too much.
title: Worked well for a year; didn’t last.

author: Becca
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2019
review_content: Be warned. Not all of the options are flat plugs. I searched for a flat plug extension cord and found this. I didn’t need the six foot so choose the 2 foot version, added it to my cart and went on my way. When it arrived, the plug was NOT flat. I went back and checked and there are various versions listed under this one product. Very confusing.
title: Not all versions are the same item

author: Dman97
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 12, 2020
review_content: I like that I was able to get this with a 10' cord so I could easily route it to where I needed it.  There are covers that can be rotated for child protection and to keep dust out of the outlets.  I also like that the protection light is noticeable but it is not too bright that it lights up the room.  There are plenty of outlets and they are nicely spaced to allow various sizes of plugs to be used.
title: Nice Long Cord

author: Cory
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 22, 2020
review_content: My apartment has some spaces blocked by furniture where it'd be convenient to have access to the outlets but would look odd with the furniture sticking out for a non-flat plug. Examples, where I've used these power strips, are in my bedroom behind the bed, and in the living room behind the TV. The individual outlets have covers which are twistable, to prevent dust and other things from touching the outlets, which is a great safety feature.
title: Flat Plug & Long Cord -- Perfect for tight spaces

author: DeepThought
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2018
review_content: However, I took one star off because the blue LED shines very brightly and is therefore a nuisance in a bedroom.  Not every power strip is installed in a well lit office.  Mine is installed behind the headboard of our bed to power our projector, Echo, and USB outlets for our phones.  Even from behind the bed, the blue LED lit up the whole room with the lights off.Simple fix: put black electrical tape over it (but I shouldn't have to is the point)
title: Fits my need well

author: megan braga
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2020
review_content: Of the six outlets, five of them didn't allow a plug to be fully inserted.  Huge fire hazard if one doesn't notice.  Not the quality I would expect, especially from a GE product.  And I choose it over Amazon Basics (and paid considerably more) because I wanted the higher quality.  Replacement one was fine, but disappointing and frustrating and makes me question the quality of other things in the surge protector.
title: Defective

author: amgross
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2021
review_content: Your browser does not support HTML5 video.           Surge protector, automatic shut down, the plugs rotate for safety if you have little ones around (can't stick things in the unused ones)  I recently had a surge in a storm and realized how important these features are.  Saved the Mac, Iphone, Apple Watch... Thank the surge protector:)
title: Surge protector, automatic shut down, the plugs rotate for safety

author: James
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 16, 2020
review_content: Really wanted to give this 5 stars, has flat plug going into the wall that also swivels. Was good the first four months. On the fifth month it started to frequently trip the internal breaker. Even narrowed it down to just 1 item(air purifier/fan) using the entire power strip. Still trips hours later, sometimes minutes later. Seemed to vary depending on ambient temps.
title: Wanted to like this...

author: J. P. Demers
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 11, 2020
review_content: This is a solidly-made device, and it will take some very serious abuse to do any damage to it.  Each socket has a rotating cover for child-proofing the outlets not in use.Only downside is the tight spacing between the outlets.  There's barely room for standard 3-prong plugs to sit side-by-side, and most "wall wart" transformers will block off at least two of them.
title: Cord is thick, case is heavy plastic - durable construction.

author: Troy Glidden
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 27, 2020
review_content: It's a surge protector, so difficult to provide a review you haven't read.  However, the flat plug is a game changer, honestly.  Gone are the days of having to keep your furniture an extra three inches from the wall.  If you use the flag plug, it's far more furniture-friendly.  Additionally, the 10-foot cable is a huge plus because it can be placed where it's needed with ease.
title: Love the flat plug

author: William Croysdill
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 1, 2020
review_content: I need an extension cord that could clear my queen size bed because the power socket is behind the head board.  The flat plug I feel is the best part as moving on the bed doesn't rub up against it and cause it to get unplugged from the wall.  I use it to charge my devices and power my computer  and it works perfectly. plugs fit nice and snug so moving it around if you have to stuff doesn't get unplugged.
title: Just what I needed

author: Annie O.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 14, 2020
review_content: I'm using this a lot more now that we're 'sheltering in place' from the coronavirus and I'm cooking nearly every day. It really is helpful. I have a tiny kitchen, with one counter that's large enough for my microwave, slow cooker and toaster.  Unfortunately, the closest outlet is placed just far enough away so that the appliances would have to be almost in the sink to be used. Now I don't have to worry!
title: Kitchen helper!

author: Serena
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 9, 2019
review_content: Others complain about what this doesn't have, but for the price I didn't expect extra features.  I just wanted a power strip and I didn't want to pay a lot for it.  This one doesn't make my TV bigger or perform other miracles.  It just works.  It has a nice, long thick power cord and the places you plug cords in swivel--for safety I guess.  If I find I need more of these which is possible with the dearth of outlets where I am living at the moment; I will not hesitate to buy another GE Power Strip just like this one.
title: Great Quality, No Miracles

author: JW
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2018
review_content: The outlets are supposed to turn when not in use to be child protected.  Several don't turn at all.  Can't get plugs in 3 of the holes without very forcefully pushing it in.  Seems to be very cheap.  Returned it.
title: Very cheap and difficult to get plugs into outlets

author: yellowspectrumxx
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 13, 2021
review_content: I like the safety feature it has where you can rotate the outlet opening to “close” it. However, the length was not long enough for what I needed. Also, I preferred to have the outlet slots arranged in the opposite way of how this one was arranged. Ended up returning it.
title: Not quite

author: Rebecca Ellen
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 15, 2020
review_content: This thing worked great for 5 months and today it started making a terrible buzzing noise and it sparked when I tried putting a plug in. It only had two plugs total. A real bummer because otherwise it was study. I loved that it has a flat plug. Sadly I’m going to by a different brand to replace this. My ikea extension cords have lasted years in comparison. I’m really disappointed.
title: Not a very long life span.

author: Rickey
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2021
review_content: Please dont risk your life and the lives of your family, this is the junkiest power strip I have ever seen, when plugging something into it you can feel how the contacts inside are loose and cheap. I could not even get a plug to fully seat into any of the outlets. Buy any other power strip over this one, this should not be UL listed, it cannot have passed any testing. GE should be sued for this product.
title: PLEASE DONT BUY THIS FIRE HAZARD

author: Amazon Customer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 21, 2020
review_content: I know this won't really protect from most truly disastrous surges... it's mostly just a multi-outlet for me. But the turnable outlets is nice, and optional covering to "close" an outlet is also a good feature. The cord is not too bendy, which is inconvenient for me trying to snake it through a cord channel but I think it reflects good quality.

author: Victoria
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 6, 2020
review_content: I needed a surge protector power strip for my sewing table that is in front of an outlet & didn’t need a long cord — I only needed more outlets. This 2ft cord is PERFECT.  I have both more outlets & surge protection for my sewing machine, lamp, iron, etc.  Although I wish it had a flat plug, it wasn’t a necessity.Item arrived in perfect condition.

author: Jennifer Bonsu
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2020
review_content: Purchased this in March and it no longer works properly. I had my netbook and lamp plugged into it, and recently the lamp started flickering. I though it was the wiring of my lamp, however when I unplugged my netbook, the light was fine. I plugged both back in, and the flickering started again, and I now here a strange humming coming from the surge protector. I do not recommend this at all
title: Poor quality

author: anonymously
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 3, 2020
review_content: The length of the cord was adequate for my needs. However, it gets very hot. I am afraid that it may be dangerous and become a fire hazard. I unplugged it and it cooled down quickly. Once again, a piece of trash purchased from Amazon.
title: Cord get hot. Possible danger

author: ryan gosling
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 1, 2021
review_content: Didn't do the ONE thing it's supposed to,  protect from electrical surges. My outlets in the kitchen aren't working and this "surge protector" did absolutely nothing. Tried the circuit breaker and the outlets still won't function.
title: Didn't protect from electrical surge.

author: Akash Malode
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 9, 2019
review_content: I was in search for an extension cord for a very long time. After reading reviews of other extension plugs, I was skeptical of this one too. But, there's nothing to be afraid of!PROS: Works like a charm. Very responsive, the ports never failed. The length of the cord is very good (suits my environment as I just need it right under my desk).  It never heats up, and I have left it switched on all through the night without any burns/hassles. It doesn't dramatically reduce the power output. Feels like I have all my appliances plugged into the wall socket. The small light isn't too bright, so it won't disturb you in the dark.CONS: just a small one (maybe just for me)- Since my adapters for my appliances are quite large, it may sometimes block the other ports. But it's not a big issue.Overall, very reliable product. Would definitely recommend!
title: Worth buying!

author: Henry
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 3, 2018
review_content: Nice length, works as advertised. Taking on star off as the blue light is a little too bright and is obnoxious. I had to stick on masking tape to hide it. 9/10Edit: Failed as of 5/19. I've had to wrap weight and tape around to keep the power on. Good while worked.
title: Power button broke.

author: Melody L
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 23, 2019
review_content: The only power outlet in my laundry room is behind the washer and dryer, so I bought this outlet strip with the nice long cord and routed it from the wall outlet through a series of Command cord clips around to the front of the dryer, where the strip is mounted to the wall.  Now I have a place I can plug in my cordless vac to charge easily, and if for any reason I need to unplug the strip the cord won't fall behind the dryer where it's unreachable.  Win!
title: Nice cord length!

author: Andra Wiegand
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 8, 2020
review_content: Maybe it works, maybe it doesn't.  I'm not going to try since I have no idea what the black stuff is.  I can't believe anyone thought sending this to a customer was okay.
title: Filthy

author: Michaela Ritschard
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 30, 2020
review_content: This was perfect for what I needed. I live in an apartment and have a TINY kitchen. We have a little room next to it that I have put a cart in that holds most of our electric appliances because our counter is too small to have anything on it. Was long enough to go from inside the kitchen to the cart, and has enough plugs for us to plug many things into it. It also is very sturdy and seems to be reliable. All in all, I am very happy with the purchase.

author: Doctor Review
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 7, 2021
review_content: I bought the protectors back in February, 2021, and it just became time to replace my current protectors.  However, I plugged in each of the purchased protectors and the blue light did not come on.  Items plugged in to the protector will work, but there is no way to check the light to properly guage if there is any real protection as opposed to just being a six-pronged outlet.  Until trying the new protectors, they were kept in their box and stored properly, so they are just seriously flawed.

author: alpop
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2020

author: Amazon Customer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 29, 2020
review_content: This is a well-made surge suppressor, which we bought for use on our deck, somewhat exposed to potential moisture.  It looks nice, and we like the protective weather flaps for each plug, but the problem is that the plugs are too close together, so if you have a power supply for a device, rather than a simple plug, it will consume 2 slots.  Overall, we like it, but I wouldn't buy this one again.

author: Chris G
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 4, 2018
review_content: When you plug something into this strip, there is a positive click that seems to lock plugs in so they don't easily partially slide out like with most other power strips I've used. Given the current discount price, I'm buying another.

author: Karen B
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 13, 2021
review_content: There are so many things I like about this item. The cord length is awesome. It has light showing on & protecting. Enough outlets for what i need and didn't inlcude the USB that I did not need. Plus with 2 in the set great value!

author: BB0183
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2021
review_content: This GE outlet by default is the best for multi purpose usage. We use it for our bathroom, garage, and dining area. The cord length is long enough for your average home usage and the thickness of the core is pretty solid. The unit itself are pretty durable

author: Jonathan Bubier
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 8, 2021
review_content: Images (looks like they changed images since then) and description show and describe flat flug. The only reason I purchased this product was for the flat plug and it does not have one. Change description and pictures in description to match the product you are offering.

author: Joseph G Costandy
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 29, 2020
review_content: I really like this power strip compared to many of the ones I've used in the past. author: B. Hansen
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 10, 2020
review_content: Two of the outlets are barely usable.  The contacts are misaligned and make it nearly impossible to insert a plug.  Very low quality product. date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2020

author: Bridget
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2020

author: Bellingham Bookworm
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 1, 2021

author: vocalion red
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 29, 2020

I don't know.

date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2020

author: AA
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 29, 2020
review_content: I screwed this to my CNC router's bench. author: Amber
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 17, 2020

author: Andrea412
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2021

date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 10, 2020

author: Alicia
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 8, 2019

author: ryobiguy

author: EricaJo

author: Lovemybaby

author: centrefrenchie
